</h3><p class="sc-edLa-Dd hZPWCc pf-28_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);"></span>Paediatric first aid stands as a cornerstone in child safety, designed to offer immediate care until professional help arrives. Data from the Health and Safety Executive (HSE) underscore the prevalence of accidents in homes and schools, many of which could be lessened or managed better with basic first aid knowledge. The Resuscitation Council (UK) emphasises the importance of prompt and effective first aid responses, which can be crucial in saving a child's life during emergencies such as choking, drowning, or sudden cardiac arrest.



<br>
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-30_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-31_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-32_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key definitions</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-34_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-35_ pf-text-1"><strong>Paediatric first aid </strong>- Medical assistance provided to an ill or injured child, involving practices adapted to their specific physiological needs.







</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-37_ pf-text-1"><strong>Basic life support (BLS) </strong>- Critical care techniques utilised in life-threatening situations before full medical treatment is available.










</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-39_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-40_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-41_ pf-heading-1-h3">Best practices in paediatric first aid</h3><p class="sc-edLa-Dd hZPWCc pf-43_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);"></span>Adopting best practices from reputable sources like the Resuscitation Council (UK) and the Health and Safety Executive, key paediatric first aid measures include:



